The White House Press Secretary, Robert Gibbs, held a press briefing on November 6, 2009. He discussed a range of topics including the Fort Hood shooting, the unemployment rate, and the ongoing debate on healthcare reform. Gibbs emphasized the need for further investigation into the motive behind the shooting and stated that the President would attend a memorial service for the victims. He also addressed concerns about the economy and job creation, stating that the President is focused on getting the economy back on track. Gibbs mentioned that the President supports the passage of the healthcare reform bill and has been making calls to urge Democrats to vote in favor of it. He also stated that the President believes the worst of the economic crisis is behind us, but that there is still work to be done to ensure economic growth and job creation.